Eyewitnesses of a horrific truck accident in Jozini in KwaZulu-Natal, are traumatised. eNCA's Siphamandla Goge has this story. Courtesy #DStv403 JOZINI - Eyewitnesses of a horrific truck accident in Jozini in KwaZulu-Natal, are traumatised. Eight people died and over 30 were injured when the truck crashed into multiple vehicles and pedestrians. READ: Six injured in Durban crash The driver reportedly claimed his brakes failed, but authorities have confirmed he was drunk. The truck driver is set to face culpable homicide charges, negligent driving, and driving under the influence of alcohol.